column10: driver of white sedan blocked crosswalk, accelerated when pedestrians walked in front, then yelled racial slurs at people who were walking

Driver speeding northbound on Montrose Ave, almost hit pedestrian in crosswalk at Evans Lane. Driver was looking at a cell phone and never realized they almost hit someone. DC tags FV3715, black sedan.

Driver turning left from westbound Glebe onto southbound US-1. Last car in a long-ish line clearly entered the intersection after light turned red and turn into the crosswalk after I had the walk light. Instead of yielding, they drove faster ~1ft away.

As I stepped in front of the car with the stroller, the driver let his foot off the brake to inch forward some more - he quickly stopped again and put his hand up apologetically while I finished crossing.

Large pickup truck rapidly approached the stop sign on Hume from route 1 and accelerated from about 30 feet before the stop sign, flooring it through the intersection with Montrose. Then turned around at top of hill and did it again toward Route 1.

The button to trigger the walk signal at E Glebe and Richmond HWY at the crosswalk going West to East does not work. Multiple full cycles of the lights are completed before you just have to find a good time to get to the median (metroway bus lane).

Our neighborhood has repeatedly asked the city for stop signs and crosswalks. Our neighborhood has many pedestrians crossing Montrose and there’s very little visibility with the parked cars. My children and I have had close calls multiple times.; Montrose,at,Evans,and,Wesmond,,cars,speeding,through,Montrose,as,a,cut,through,from,Rte,1,to,Glebe; No,crosswalks
People don’t yield to pedestrians in the crosswalk and frequently speed along Glebe.

Parked cars on Montrose create terrible sight lines for vehicles entering/exiting Montrose. That curve on Montrose should prohibit parking on at least one – if not both sides; Parked,cars,on,Montrose,create,terrible,sight,lines,for,vehicles,entering/exiting,Montrose.

Drivers frequently speed on Glebe road, and they routinely fail to yield to pedestrians. One of my neighbors works from home and reports hearing at least 3 near-misses per day and has heard multiple accidents.; My,neighborhood,discusses,this,frequently,on,our,listserv,,and,the,city,has,so,far,been,deaf,to,multiple,years,of,requests,for,a,5-way,stop,sign,there.; This,intersection,is,AWFUL.,Only,3,of,the,5,entrances,into,the,intersection,have,to,stop.,Of,these,,one,cannot,see,cross,traffic,from,the,right.

The walk light comes after the left turn light for drivers turning from westbound E Glebe onto southbound Richmond Hyw. The left turners routinely continue turning after their light turns red. The walk signal only lasts 2 sec. longer walk signal please.
Driver made eye contact with pedestrians and entered crosswalk making a right turn, disregarding pedestrian presence and brushing against pedestrians with vehicle. DC tags, FV 4238, silver SUV
Drivers blocking crosswalk
White Honda with female driver in her 20s turned right on red while I was in the crosswalk, coming within about 2 inches of running over my foot
As per usual, the intersection was blocked by people stopping in the crosswalk. It would be great if the APD would step up enforcement here.
Driver speeding down Montrose Ave failed to stop for pedestrians in crosswalk.

White sedan and black SUV blocked crosswalk. Black SUV accelerated while pedestrians were in crosswalk, almost striking a pedestrian. Driver of the white sedan opened window and started shouting at pedestrians, ending with racial epithets.
Westbound car did not even notice that there was a stop sign as she looked down while driving into the low sun.
Construction-related vehicle parked blocking the sidewalk and the eastbound travel lane (no parking zone).
This intersection is very dangerous. Pedestrians in crosswalk are completely unprotected across five lanes or traffic plus two bus lanes.

Driving south on Montrose Ave, I came to a complete stop at the stop sign at Raymond Ave. As I started pulling out, an SUV moving *very* fast approached from the east (hidden by a parked SUV) and blew thru the stop sign, swerving to avoid my nose.
Driver almost ran over 2 people & 3 dogs as they aggressively turned right from eastbound Glebe onto southbound US-1. Stopped with 1 Ft of one of the dogs.
driver ignored flashing lights and blew through crosswalk while speeding
This is an incredibly dangerous intersection where some directions stop and others don’t. Have been in multiple near misses here.
Employees of R. Bratti park in a manner that partially obstructs the sidewalk.
People at the stone supply always block the sidewalk when parked
Custruction-related vehicle (no indication of permits) parked in a no-parking zone (eastbound lane) and entirely blocking the sidewalk

A speeding car (50+ mph) drove into the left turn lane, in order to bypass line of cars stopped at solid red light on Rt. 1, so that he could blow through the red light and continue down Rt. 1. There was a person walking a bicycle across Rt. 1 that was almost hit.
column21: This type of reckless driving is common on Rt.1 and this particular incident was disquieting - if hit, the pedestrian surely would have died.
